<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pringle</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-14"><hi rend="italic">March 14,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Peterson informs that Imboden and Barnharts are confined, and will be
                            obliged to leave the country. Government of Honduras wishes to deal with
                            party duly authorized to treat. <hi rend="italic">Ranger</hi> still
                            here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pringle.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>